XML vs JSON
----   -----

XML = Extensible Markup language

1. It is simply a markup language (Tag based language)
2. It is heavy weight (limitation)
3. Data transfer Format
4. Its a language independent
5. It does not support the concept of array(limitation)

<movies>
    <movie>
        <movie-name>Adventure</movie-name>
        <movie-comment>3 Rotten Tomatoes</movie-comment> 
        <movie-rating>2.4</movie-rating>
        <movie-actor>John Jackson</movie-actor>
    </movie>
    <movie>
        <movie-name>Adventure</movie-name>
        <movie-comment>3 Rotten Tomatoes</movie-comment> 
        <movie-rating>2.4</movie-rating>
        <movie-actor>John Jackson</movie-actor>
    </movie>
    <movie>
        <movie-name>Adventure</movie-name>
        <movie-comment>3 Rotten Tomatoes</movie-comment> 
        <movie-rating>2.4</movie-rating>
        <movie-actor>John Jackson</movie-actor>
    </movie>
</movies>

JSON = JavaScript Object Notation

1. It consists of key value pair.
    {key : value}

2. It is light weight (advantage)
3. Data transfer Format
4. Its a language independent
5. It supports the concept of array(advantage)

[
    {
        "movie_name":"Adventure",
        "movie_comment" : "3 Rotten Tomatoes",
        "movie_rating" : 2.4,
        "movie_actor" : "John Jackson"
    },
    {
        "movie_name":"Adventure",
        "movie_comment" : "3 Rotten Tomatoes",
        "movie_rating" : 2.4,
        "movie_actor" : "John Jackson"
    },
    {
        "movie_name":"Adventure",
        "movie_comment" : "3 Rotten Tomatoes",
        "movie_rating" : 2.4,
        "movie_actor" : "John Jackson"
    },
    {
        "movie_name":"Adventure",
        "movie_comment" : "3 Rotten Tomatoes",
        "movie_rating" : 2.4,
        "movie_actor" : "John Jackson"
    },
    {
        "movie_name":"Adventure",
        "movie_comment" : "3 Rotten Tomatoes",
        "movie_rating" : 2.4,
        "movie_actor" : "John Jackson"
    }
]



var obj = {
    name : "andrew anderson",
    age : 67
}

var json = {
    "name" : "Andrew Anderson",
    "age" : 67
}